    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.30-32_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">30</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ATLANTA     CHICAGO     DALLAS      SAN FRANCISCO       LONDON      MANILA
                        <lb/>
                    BRETT-MACMILLAN, TORONTO
                        <lb/>
                        
                    THE MACMILLAN COMPANY
                        <lb/>
                        
                    CABLE ADDRESS
                    PACHAMAC NEW YORK</hi>
                    
                    <hi rend="italics">Publishers</hi>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 
                    OREGON 5-4000
                        <lb/>
                        
                    SIXTY ∙ FIFTH AVENUE  ∙ NEW YORK 11,N.Y.
                        <lb/>
                        
                    GEORGE P. BRETT, JR., PRESIDENT             BRUCE Y. BRETT, VICE PRESIDENT &amp; SECRETARY          ADRIAN A. DAY, TREASURER
                        <lb/>
                                        JOSEPH B. BENNETT, JR., VICE PRESIDENT                      FAULKNER LEWIS, VICE PRESIDENT</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 15, 1957</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>I am writing about some past history, which must now be resolved. You may recall back in 1956 having made an arrangement directly with Andrew Melrose, the English publisher, for a cheap edition, by Panther Books, of <hi rend="caps">EAGLE VOICE (WHEN THE TREE FLOWERED)</hi>. The facts seem to be that Panther was granted British Empire rights, exlcluding Canada, for a period of three years, and the advnace was to be £100--£50 on signing and £50 on publication--against a royalty of 2-5/8d. on home sales, and 2-3/16d. on export sales. Your agreement with Melrose was to split the sum fifty-fifty.</p>
                
                <p>As you are also aware, this arrangement was made without the knowledge at the time of either Curtis Brown or ourselves, and it does present an embarrassing situation.</p>
                
                <p>We have now received an accounting from Melrose, which indicates that the sales have been as follows
                    <lb/>
                Regular sales       11,065                   £121.9.5 1/2
                    <lb/>
                Export sales         7,149<hi rend="underline">65.3.2 1/2</hi>
                    <lb/>
                                     Total royalty earned - £186.12.8
                </p> 
                
                <p>The net sum which we received after the deducation<sic>deduction</sic> of the agent's commission and the Melrose 50% is $173.35. Under the terms of our contract with you, these net proceeds are to be divided equally. Therefore, the amount which is owed to you is $86.68. It is a pleasure to send a check for that amount with this letter.</p>
                
                <p>We regret exceedingly that the situation has become so complicated, but in view of the singular circumstances surrounding the original arrangement with Melrose, I am afraid the results have been inescapable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With all good wishes,</salute>
                    
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>J.P.R. Budlong</signed>
                    
                    <signed>J. P. R. Budlong
                    Director, Trade Department</signed>
                    
                    <note>JPRB:KK</note>
                    <note>Encl.</note>
                </closer>
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="enclosure">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.30-32_0006"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">31</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps"><unclear/>RM 52RY 5M 7-57
                        <lb/>
                    <del>ANNUAL</del> STATEMENT OF ROYALTY ACCOUNT
                        <lb/>
                    THE MACMILLAN COMPANY
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italics">PUBLISHERS</hi>  
                        <lb/>
                    60 FIFTH AVENUE, NEW YORK 11, N. Y.</hi></fw> <opener><dateline><hi rend="caps">NOV</hi> 15 1957</dateline>
               
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi>Neihardt,</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Route #6,</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </opener>
                <p><hi rend="italics">By Royalty <del>for fiscal year ending April 30th, 19</del>          on your book</hi>
                <add>When the Tree Flowered.</add>                                          <hi rend="italics">Copies @</hi>
                <add>50% of amount received on English Edition.                  $8668</add></p>
                
                <note><hi rend="caps">O.K.</hi> <unclear/></note>
               
                <p><hi rend="caps">DELIVER CHECK AND STATEMENT TO</hi> Mr. Budlong</p>
                   
                <p><figure><figDesc>A Pointing Hand</figDesc></figure><add>A</add> <hi rend="caps">PLEASE NOTE THAT THE ABOVE IS DUE AND PAYABLE <add>NOV 15 1957</add>
                KINDLY OBLIGE BY FILING THIS STATEMENT FOR REFERENCE</hi></p>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.30-32_0002"/>
                
